cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with per-pixel semantic segmentation/detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the issue of data imbalance, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and the proposed approach involves end-to-end training, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
